{"questionId":"13975738","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The computer then selects at random an integer <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>, inclusive. Each outcome is equally likely.</p>\n<p>Daniel is trying to determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> and asks if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>. He is told that it is not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> when the expected information gained is maximized.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use graphical method or calculus to maximize&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mfenced><mi>I</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0b6e49ef158a8efddc89ff84fccac9ee911ca94f.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">maximum occurs when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13975738","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2diii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, find the value of p when the expected information gained is maximized.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
